# 2. PRD & DESIGN REFERENCES
# ============================================================

## PRD Reference
The full PRD is in /docs/PRD.md and covers:
- Problem: home cooks waste 15-30 min deciding what to cook
- Target user: amateur home cooks managing kitchen ingredients
- 5 core user stories (see below)
- Acceptance criteria for each story

## Design System
Primary color:   Orange / Amber (#f59e0b — Tailwind: amber-500)
Secondary color: Green (#22c55e — Tailwind: green-500)
Background:      White (#ffffff)
Text:            Gray-900 for headings, Gray-600 for body
Borders:         Orange for active/current items, Green for suggested/positive items
Animations:      300ms ease-in-out opacity transitions on all interactive elements
Corner radius:   rounded-lg on cards, rounded-full on badges/tags
Font:            System font stack (no custom fonts required)

## Key UI Components
- RecipeCard: Shows recipe name, thumbnail, difficulty badge, prep/cook time,
  and ingredient match % (e.g. "85% match"). Perfect matches get a green border.
  Near-matches get an amber border. Cards are fully clickable.
- IngredientCard: Clickable box showing ingredient name in capitalized format.
  Current pantry items have orange borders with a minus icon.
  Suggested items have green borders with a plus icon.
- FilterPanel: Slide-out panel triggered by filter icon in header.
  Contains checkboxes for cuisine type and dietary restrictions.
  Active filters show as dismissible badges in the header.
- Header: Sticky, consistent across all pages. Always shows hamburger menu icon
  and filter icon. Logo/title is clickable and navigates to homepage.
- Toast Notifications: Orange theme, appear for all pantry/list actions.
  Auto-dismiss after 3 seconds.
- Confirmation Modal: Appears before any destructive action (e.g. clear grocery list).
  Has Cancel and Confirm buttons. Backdrop click dismisses.

## User Flows (implement features in this order of priority)
1. New user registers → logs in → lands on homepage with empty pantry prompt
2. User navigates to Pantry → searches ingredients → adds to inventory
3. Homepage recipe grid updates to show match percentages based on pantry
4. User clicks recipe card → views full detail → marks as cooked
5. Cooking log entry is clickable and navigates back to recipe detail
6. Smart suggestions show top ingredients to buy to unlock more recipes
7. User adds suggested ingredients to grocery list → moves all to pantry

## Pages Summary
- / (Home):         Filterable recipe grid with match percentages
- /pantry:          Three sections — Suggested, Current Inventory, Grocery List
- /recipes/[id]:    Full recipe detail with ingredients, steps, and "Mark as Cooked"
- /history:         Chronological cooking log with clickable entries

